<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36096e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36096e">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36096e"> 96(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Bang-beggar</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">There was a special vestry whose function it was to issue licences to paupers to beg, and a parish officer, known as &ldquo;<mark>Bang-beggar</mark>&rdquo;, was appointed to supervise the practice of this profession in the town, and to repress sternly any poaching by unlicensed members of the craft. <small> Weston St. John Joyce, <a name="WSJ1" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#WSJ1"><cite title="source">The Neighbourhood of Dublin</cite></a> (1921) 205</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
